msgstr "Conclusion: Ascend lacks fp64 support compared to GPU."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:24
msgid "#### 2.2.2 Shape 支持"
msgstr "#### 2.2.2 Shape Support"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:26
msgid ""
"|        | 支持维度范围          |\n"
"| ------ | --------------- |\n"
"| GPU    | 仅支持 1~5维 tensor |\n"
"| Ascend A2/A3 | 仅支持 1~5维 tensor |\n"
msgstr ""
"|        | Supported Dimension Range |\n"
"| ------ | ----------------------- |\n"
"| GPU    | Only supports 1~5D tensor |\n"
"| Ascend A2/A3 | Only supports 1~5D tensor |\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:28
msgid "结论：在 Shape 方面，GPU 与 Ascend 平台无差异，均支持 1 至 5 维张量。"
msgstr "Conclusion: In terms of Shape, there is no difference between GPU and Ascend platforms, both supporting tensors from 1 to 5 dimensions."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:30
msgid "### 2.3 特殊限制说明"
msgstr "### 2.3 Special Restrictions Explanation"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:32
msgid "> 相对社区能力缺失且无法实现"
msgstr "Relative community capacity deficiency and inability to achieve"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:34
msgid "无。"
msgstr "None."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:36
msgid "#### 2.3.1 propagate_nan 参数限制"
msgstr "#### 2.3.1 propagate_nan Parameter Constraints"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:38
msgid "**注意：当 `propagate_nan=tl.PropagateNAN.NONE` 时，系统会自动添加 NaN 值处理逻辑，这会导致：**"
msgstr "**Note: When `propagate_nan=tl.PropagateNAN.NONE`, the system will automatically add NaN value handling logic, which will result in:**"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:40
msgid ""
"1. **UB 空间使用增加**：额外的 NaN 检测和处理需要占用更多的 UB 空间\n"
"2. **可能的性能下降**：由于增加了额外的计算逻辑，可能导致算子执行性能下降\n"
msgstr ""
"1. **Increased UB Space Usage**: Additional NaN detection and handling requires more UB space.  \n"
"2. **Potential Performance Degradation**: The added computational logic may lead to reduced operator execution performance.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:42
msgid "**建议：**"
msgstr "**Recommendation:**"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:44
msgid ""
"- 如果输入数据不包含 NaN 值，或不需要严格的 NaN 处理语义，建议使用默认值或根据实际需求选择合适的 `propagate_nan` 参数值\n"
"- 在 UB 空间紧张的场景下，应特别注意此参数的选择，避免因 UB 空间不足导致编译失败\n"
msgstr ""
"- If the input data does not contain NaN values or does not require strict NaN handling semantics, it is recommended to use the default value or select an appropriate `propagate_nan` parameter value based on actual needs.  \n"
"- In scenarios where UB space is limited, special attention should be paid to the selection of this parameter to avoid compilation failures caused by insufficient UB space.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:46
msgid "### 2.4 使用方法"
msgstr "### 2.4 Usage"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:48
msgid "以下示例实现了对输入张量 `x` 和`y`的逐元素最小值："
msgstr "The following example implements the element-wise minimum of input tensors `x` and `y`:"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Math_Ops/minimum.md:50
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"@triton.jit\n"
"def fn_npu_(output_ptr, x_ptr, y_ptr,\n"
"            XB: tl.constexpr, YB: tl.constexpr, ZB: tl.constexpr,\n"
"            XNUMEL: tl.constexpr, YNUMEL: tl.constexpr, ZNUMEL: tl.constexpr):\n"
"    xoffs = tl.program_id(0) * XB\n"
"    yoffs = tl.program_id(1) * YB\n"
"    zoffs = tl.program_id(2) * ZB\n"
"\n"
"    xidx = tl.arange(0, XB) + xoffs\n"
"    yidx = tl.arange(0, YB) + yoffs\n"
"    zidx = tl.arange(0, ZB) + zoffs\n"
"\n"
"    idx = xidx[:, None, None] * YNUMEL * ZNUMEL + yidx[None, :, None] * ZNUMEL + zidx[None, None, :]\n"
"\n"
"    X = tl.load(x_ptr + idx)\n"
"    Y = tl.load(y_ptr + idx)\n"
"\n"
"    ret = tl.minimum(X, Y)\n"
"\n"
"    tl.store(output_ptr + idx, ret)\n"
"\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

